    "rationale": "The Wacker oxidation of ethylene to acetaldehyde is the original industrial process and the quintessential textbook example of this reaction. It clearly demonstrates the conversion of a terminal alkene to a carbonyl compound (an aldehyde in this specific case, though methyl ketones are more common from higher alkenes) using a palladium catalyst (PdCl2) and a co-catalyst/reoxidant system (CuCl/O2). This example is simple, acyclic, and perfectly illustrates the core transformation of the Wacker oxidation.",
